<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,583,608]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1959" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[620,931,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis box="[620,779,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. darlingtoni</emphasis>
Evans, 1959
</taxonomicName>
by having the clypeus truncate at its apical margin and with the clypeal carina wide; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the frons strongly punctured; and the pronotal disc strongly punctured, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[632,790,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darlingtoni">
<emphasis box="[632,790,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. darlingtoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeus with its median lobe rounded, short, and with the clypeal carina narrow; the antennal scrobe carinate; the frons 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[998,1121,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
; and the pronotal disc not punctured.
</paragraph>
